the game play is solid, a bit to flashy for me, but it makes sense for game that has a wildly popular anime series behind it.  it's smooth. 

there is a lot of clicking, you click to get to phases and to attack and to summon and to spell cast and trap and all that.

there is a premium, a small one on foil cards that get traded out.  but it's better the the PTCGO trading system and better than eternal and hearthstones rate.  It's much better than the wildcard system because you don't have to sit on dead stuff, you can make it real cards!

the mission system gives you a lot of in game currency, and there are a lot of cards on the client.  Like a ton.  The crafting system is easy to understand, you basically three of one rarity for the same rarity.  so 3 Srs you don't want become one that you do want.

Okay so the yu-gi-oh client is nice.  A really nice tutorial system.  I say I don't have any idea of what is happening, but I have  a pretty good idea of how to actually play the game.  the solo features of the game look like they give you a lot to do!
